==Estonian==
===Etymology===
A compound of üh- and -eksa. The former comes from [[üks]], while the latter is from an original *''deksa'', which is from an Iranian language, compare Kurdish [[deh]]. So the compound originally meant one (from) ten.
===Cardinal number===
'''üheksa'''

#[[nine]]

